---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Refund Policy — Envoyou Company"
  description="Refund and payment dispute policy for Envoyou prepaid plans and credits."
>
  <Navbar />

  <main class="min-h-screen bg-bg pt-28 pb-20 relative overflow-hidden transition-colors duration-300">
    <!-- Ambient Radial Glows -->
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_30%_10%,rgba(11,121,194,0.04),transparent_40%),radial-gradient(circle_at_70%_20%,rgba(147,51,234,0.03),transparent_40%)]"></div>

    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
      <!-- Title Header -->
      <div class="mb-12 border-b border-border pb-8 text-center sm:text-left">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-extrabold uppercase tracking-widest text-primary bg-primary/10 px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-primary/20 mb-4">
          Billing & Payments
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-text mb-4">Refund Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
          Last Updated: June 23, 2026. This policy applies to prepaid EAI plans and additional credit purchases processed through our supported payment gateways.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Legal Content Sections -->
      <div class="space-y-10 text-sm sm:text-base text-text/80 leading-relaxed max-w-none">

        <section id="prepaid-purchases" class="space-y-3 group scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold text-text tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">1.</span> Prepaid Purchases
          </h2>
          <p>
            EAI plans and add-ons are prepaid. Automatic recurring billing is not
            currently enabled. Monthly and annual access begins when payment is
            confirmed and the corresponding credits are allocated.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="refund-eligibility" class="space-y-3 group scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold text-text tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">2.</span> Refund Eligibility
          </h2>
          <p>You may request review of a refund when:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li>you were charged more than once for the same intended purchase;</li>
            <li>payment succeeded but EAI did not allocate the purchased plan or credits;</li>
            <li>the amount charged did not match the confirmed checkout amount;</li>
            <li>the transaction was unauthorized, subject to identity verification; or</li>
            <li>a refund is required by applicable consumer law.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            You may also request cancellation of a substantially unused purchase
            within seven calendar days of payment. We will review usage, allocated
            benefits, payment-provider limitations, and applicable law before
            approving or declining the request.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="purchases-generally-not-refundable" class="space-y-3 group scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold text-text tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">3.</span> Purchases Generally Not Refundable
          </h2>
          <p>
            Except where required by law, we generally do not refund credits that
            have already been consumed, completed editorial processing, change of
            mind after substantial use, dissatisfaction caused solely by content that
            was not human-reviewed, or suspension resulting from a material breach of
            the Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="failed-pending-or-duplicate-transactions" class="space-y-3 group scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold text-text tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">4.</span> Failed, Pending, or Duplicate Transactions
          </h2>
          <p>
            A failed or expired checkout does not allocate credits. A pending bank or
            wallet authorization may be released automatically by the payment
            provider. For duplicate successful payments, contact us with both order
            references so we can verify the records.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="how-to-request-a-refund" class="space-y-3 group scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold text-text tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">5.</span> How to Request a Refund
          </h2>
          <p>
            Submit a tracked request through the <a href="https://eai.envoyou.com/support" class="text-primary hover:underline">EAI support form</a>{' '}
            or email <a href="mailto:support@envoyou.com" class="text-primary hover:underline">support@envoyou.com</a>{' '}
            with your account email, organization name, order or invoice number,
            payment date, amount, and reason. Do not send card numbers, PINs,
            passwords, or one-time codes.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="review-and-payment-return" class="space-y-3 group scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold text-text tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">6.</span> Review and Payment Return
          </h2>
          <p>
            We aim to acknowledge complete requests within three business days.
            Approved refunds are returned through a method supported by the original
            payment provider. Bank, wallet, and provider processing times may apply.
            Refunded credits and related plan access may be removed from the account.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="chargebacks-and-fraud" class="space-y-3 group scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold text-text tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">7.</span> Chargebacks and Fraud
          </h2>
          <p>
            Contact us before initiating a chargeback so we can investigate. We may
            suspend disputed credits or account access while an unauthorized payment,
            fraud report, or chargeback is reviewed.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="plan-changes-and-remaining-credits" class="space-y-3 group scroll-mt-28">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold text-text tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">8.</span> Plan Changes and Remaining Credits
          </h2>
          <p>
            Purchasing a different plan does not automatically refund a previous
            purchase. Monthly plan credits are tied to their purchased period, annual
            credits to the annual prepaid period, and separately purchased add-on
            credits currently do not expire.
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
